-- Manchester United Beats Newcastle 3-0 in League; Spurs Win
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-10-07T16:55:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-07/manchester-united-beats-newcastle-3-0-in-league-spurs-win.html
Manchester United won 3-0 at
Newcastle today to climb to second in English soccer’s Premier
League, while Tottenham beat Aston Villa 2-0 for its fourth
straight victory in the competition.  Jonny Evans,  Patrice Evra  and Tom Cleverley scored for
United, which sits above rival Manchester City on goal
difference. Chelsea holds a four-point lead over both clubs.  In today’s other games, Liverpool was held to a 0-0 home
draw by Stoke, while Southampton and Fulham tied 2-2.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  